From: Kefu Chai <k.chai@proxmox.com>
Date: Tue, 26 May 2026 23:30:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] debian/rules: disable RBD persistent caches for the crimson
 build profile

The crimson build profile does not exercise librbd's persistent
write-log cache (WITH_RBD_RWL) or SSD cache (WITH_RBD_SSD_CACHE).
Both options pull in PMDK via Buildpmdk.cmake's network-dependent
ExternalProject_Add (GIT_REPOSITORY https://github.com/ceph/pmdk.git),
which is a frequent build-time failure point.

Disable both when building the crimson profile. cmake honours
last-wins for repeated -D options on the command line, so appending
=OFF after the earlier =ON cleanly overrides without needing to
delete the existing lines (non-crimson builds keep them unchanged).

Signed-off-by: Kefu Chai <k.chai@proxmox.com>
---
 debian/rules | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/debian/rules b/debian/rules
--- a/debian/rules
+++ b/debian/rules
@@ -36,6 +36,15 @@ else
   extraopts += -DWITH_RBD_RWL=OFF
 endif
 extraopts += -DWITH_RBD_SSD_CACHE=ON
+
+# Crimson does not use BlueStore persistent-memory features or
+# librbd's persistent caches; force them off when building the
+# crimson profile to skip Buildpmdk.cmake's network-dependent
+# GIT_REPOSITORY fetch of github.com/ceph/pmdk.git.
+ifneq ($(filter pkg.ceph.crimson,$(DEB_BUILD_PROFILES)),)
+  extraopts += -DWITH_RBD_RWL=OFF
+  extraopts += -DWITH_RBD_SSD_CACHE=OFF
+endif
 # assumes that ceph is exmpt from multiarch support, so we override the libdir.
 extraopts += -DCMAKE_INSTALL_LIBDIR=/usr/lib
 extraopts += -DCMAKE_INSTALL_LIBEXECDIR=/usr/libexec
